{"type":"message","id":"1845c409","parentId":"65c413c0","timestamp":"2026-03-30T07:40:24.439Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user is saying they only have 25 stocks. This is a follow-up to the previous question about the 45 vs 25 stocks. The user is confirming their actual holding is 25 stocks.\n\nThe issue is that the daily execution card (每日执行卡) is reading from `account_holdings_20260330.csv` which has 45 entries (40 A-shares + 4 HK stocks + 1 ETF), but the user only has 25 stocks in their paper portfolio.\n\nThe correct source should be `paper_portfolio_positions_latest.csv` which has 25 stocks.\n\nLet me look at the `build_daily_quant_analysis_json.py` script more carefully to understand where the `position_count` comes from and how it gets aggregated.\n\n\nLooking at the panel data, the position_count field shows 27 total positions across the different groups (exit_dual, exit_tight, breadth_strict_oos, breadth_aggressive, and legacy_paper), but the user is saying they only have 25 stocks in their actual paper portfolio. This suggests the position counts are being aggregated from multiple sleeves rather than reflecting the actual consolidated holdings.\n\nThe issue is that `paper_portfolio_positions_latest.csv` with 25 entries is the correct source for the user's actual positions, but the daily execution card appears to be reading from `account_holdings_20260330.csv` which contains 45 entries including other sleeves. I need to trace through the `generate_control_tower_daily.py` script to see where it's pulling position data from.","thinkingSignature":"a406c2eeae7ae14a9b3802a2673ad55a54d9ab37835388c39f83329f2256c6f3"},{"type":"text","text":"收到，25只是正确的。我来快速定位问题并修复。\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_5db2bljdwnwk_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"grep -n \"position_count\\|holdings_count\\|A 股\\|A股\\|45\" /Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/quant_projects/personal-a-share-research-system/scripts/generate_cont