{"type":"message","id":"1176b55d","parentId":"8f65ae61","timestamp":"2026-03-30T07:41:54.680Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_540fhwwwsm00_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"        status_class = {\n            \"GREEN\": \"status-green\",\n            \"YELLOW\": \"status-yellow\",\n            \"RED\": \"status-red\",\n        }.get(str(row[\"status\"]), \"\")\n        profile_cards.append(\n            f\"\"\"<article class=\"card {status_class}\">\n              <div class=\"label\">{html.escape(row['profile_slug'])}</div>\n              <div class=\"value\">{html.escape(str(row['status']))}</div>\n              <div class=\"minor\">mode={html.escape(str(row['tomorrow_mode']))} | issues={html.escape(row['issue_codes'] or 'none')}</div>\n              <div class=\"metric-grid\">\n                <div><span>净值</span><strong>{row['nav']:.2f}</strong></div>\n                <div><span>累计收益</span><strong>{row['total_return_pct']:.2f}%</strong></div>\n                <div><span>回撤</span><strong>{row['drawdown_pct']:.2f}%</strong></div>\n                <div><span>持仓数</span><strong>{int(row.get('position_count', 0))}</strong></div>\n              </div>\n            </article>\"\"\"\n        )\n\n    breadth_alert = payload[\"profit_layer\"].get(\"breadth_alert\", {}) or {}\n    breadth_issue_codes = \",\".join(breadth_alert.get(\"issue_codes\") or []) or \"none\"\n    breadth_alert_status = str(breadth_alert.get(\"status\") or \"NO_DATA\")\n    breadth_alert_card_class = {\n        \"GREEN\": \"status-green\",\n        \"YELLOW\": \"status-yellow\",\n        \"RED\": \"status-red\",\n    }.get(breadth_alert_status, \"\")\n    breadth_alert_minor = (\n        f\"issues={html.escape(breadth_issue_codes)} | drift={html.escape(str(breadth_alert.get('target_drift_pct', '-')))}%\"\n    )\n    governance_status = str(payload[\"strategy_layer\"].get(\"governance_status\") or \"UNKNOWN\")\n    governance_card_class = \"status-green\" if governance_status == \"PASS\" else \"status-red\"\n    governance_issues = payload[\"strategy_layer\"].get(\"governance_blocking_issues\") or []\n\n    return f\"\"\"<!doctype html>\n<html lang=\"zh-CN\">\n<head>\n  <meta charset=\"utf-8\" />\n  <meta name=\"viewport\" content=\"width=device-width, initial-scale=1\" />\n  <title>控制塔日报</title>\n  <style>\n    :root {{\n      --bg: #f3f6f8; --paper:#fff; --ink:#0f1720; --muted:#627080; --line:#dbe3ea;\n      --green:#146c43; --yellow:#b7791f; --red:#c0392b; --blue:#174ea6;\n    }}\n    * {{ box-sizing:border-box; }}\n    body {{ margin:0; background:\n      linear-gradient(135deg, rgba(23,78,166,.08), transparent 35%),\n      linear-gradient(180deg, #fbfdff, var(--bg)); font-family:\"SF Pro Display\",\"PingFang SC\",sans-serif; color:var(--ink); }}\n    .wrap {{ max-width:1360px; margin:0 auto; padding:28px; }}\n\n[143 more lines in file. Use offset=905 to continue.]"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774856514665}}
{"type":"message","id":"6b2f697d","parentId":"1176b55d","timestamp":"2026-03-30T07:42:05.290Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The HTML card shows `position_count` from the row data. Now I need to find where the \"A股 45 只\" text comes from in the daily execution card. Let me look at the `render_daily_quant_analysis_md.py` to see how it generates the text summary that gets sent to Feishu.Let me actually look at what the daily execution card shows - the user showed the text starting with \"📋 每日执行卡 v2\". This card was generated by `build_daily_quant_analysis_json.py` which creates the JSON, and then `render_daily_quant_analysis_feishu.py` renders it to text. \n\nI'm not finding \"45\" directly in the scripts, so the count must be computed dynamically from the holdings data. Looking at the code flow, `position_count` comes from the strategy_performance_panel, but that shows 27, not 45. The discrepancy suggests the daily execution card is aggregating holdings differently—maybe summing across all sub-portfolios or using a different data source than what I'm tracing through the panel.","thinkingSignature":"6c794c21d1559ecfcb60e8abeb423b7a2ba7980ee8e3f192835b103baaa43464"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_yb6fcrv96hln_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"python3 -c \"\nimport json\nwith open('/Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/quant_projects/personal-a-share-research-system/research/reports/daily_quant_analysis_skill_latest.json') as f:\n    d = json.load(f)\nph = d.get('profile_holdings') or []\ntotal = 0\nfor entry in ph:\n    pc = entry.get('position_count', 0)\n    holdings = entry.get('holdings') or []\n    print(f'{entry.get(\\\"profile_slug\\\")} ({entry.get(\\\"group\\\")}): position_count={pc}, actual_holdings={len(holdings)}')\n    total += len(holdings)\nprint(f'Total actual holdings in profile_holdings: {total}')\n\""}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":3