{"type":"message","id":"df667344","parentId":"8c9f82fc","timestamp":"2026-03-30T07:45:45.812Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I need to verify the fix by running the script. Let me also check if the `paper_portfolio_positions_latest.csv` has a quantity column that can be parsed correctly.Actually wait - I need to also look at the format of `paper_portfolio_positions_latest.csv`. It has:\n```\nsymbol,asset_type,name,quantity,cost_price\n```\n\nAnd the `norm_h` function maps:\n- `ts_code` or `symbol` → `symbol` ✓\n- `name` → `name` ✓\n- `qty` or `quantity` → `quantity` ✓\n- `asset_type` → `asset_type` ✓\n\n\n- `currency` → `currency` (defaults to CNY from norm_h)\n- `cost_price` → `cost_price` ✓\n\nWith my `_infer_currency_and_asset_type` fix, HK stocks will be detected by `.HK` suffix and marked as HKD currency with stock asset type, while ETFs will be inferred from the symbol prefixes and names. The script should now handle both CSV formats correctly, so let me run it to test.","thinkingSignature":"ddad1c66f828a13ff3fa9bcc46cd01f22af84393b88d30e3d2ef7794187f517e"},{"type":"text","text":"现在运行验证一下：\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_uquikpk2kmpm_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cd /Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace && python3 scripts/generate_daily_exec_card.py 2>&1 | tail -30","timeout":30}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":56350,"output":294,"cacheRead":25093,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":81737,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774856736839,"responseId":"06195d21a77cf30faa4e194ba934d5d5"}}
